# Nekretnine PRO – Serbian Real Estate Market Analytics

Interactive web application for geospatial analysis, price prediction, and opportunity detection on the Serbian residential property market (sale and rental).

[![Python 3.9+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
![GitHub stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/MilosMajkic/nekretnine-pro?style=social)
![GitHub forks](https://img.shields.io/github/forks/MilosMajkic/nekretnine-pro?style=social)
![GitHub watchers](https://img.shields.io/github/watchers/MilosMajkic/nekretnine-pro?style=social)

## Features

- Interactive geospatial map (Folium + MarkerCluster + HeatMap + Draw tools)
- 3D density visualization (PyDeck HexagonLayer)
- Machine-learning price prediction (Random Forest)
- Value scoring: "Golden opportunities" (≤ 85% of predicted value) and "suspiciously low" (≤ 45%)
- Approximate Walk Score based on distance to city center
- Comprehensive filtering: city, price, price/m², floor area, distance
- Favorites system for saving and comparing listings
- Location A/B comparison module
- Support for both sale and rental market datasets

## Technology Stack

| Layer                | Technology                               |
|----------------------|------------------------------------------|
| Web Framework        | Streamlit                                |
| Geospatial           | Folium · streamlit-folium · PyDeck       |
| Data Processing      | pandas · numpy                           |
| Machine Learning     | scikit-learn (RandomForestRegressor)     |
| Clustering & Heatmap | folium.plugins (MarkerCluster, HeatMap)  |
| Distance             | Haversine formula                        |
| State Management     | streamlit.session_state                  |

## Installation

1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/MilosMajkic/nekretnine-pro.git
cd nekretnine-pro

Create virtual environment

Bashpython -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate      # Linux/macOS
# or on Windows:
# .venv\Scripts\activate

Install dependencies

Bashpip install -r requirements.txt
Typical requirements.txt:
textstreamlit>=1.31.0
pandas>=2.0
numpy>=1.24
scikit-learn>=1.3
folium>=0.14.0
streamlit-folium>=0.17.0
pydeck>=0.8.0

Prepare input data

Place CSV files in the project root:

nekretnina_srb_geo.csv     (sale listings)
izdavanje_srb_geo.csv      (rental listings)

Required / recommended columns:

Grad, Deo_Grada, Ulica
Cena_EUR, Kvadratura_m2, Cena_po_m2
Naslov, Link
Latitude, Longitude


Run the application

Bashstreamlit run app.py
Continuous Integration (GitHub Actions)
Basic linting + dependency check workflow (.github/workflows/ci.yml):
YAMLname: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  lint-and-test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
    - uses: actions/checkout@v4

    - name: Set up Python 3.11
      uses: actions/setup-python@v5
      with:
        python-version: '3.11'

    - name: Install dependencies
      run: |
        python -m pip install --upgrade pip
        pip install -r requirements.txt
        pip install ruff pytest

    - name: Lint with Ruff
      run: ruff check . --output-format=github

    - name: Run tests (if any)
      run: pytest
      continue-on-error: true
Deployment
Recommended platforms (easiest → more control):

Streamlit Community Cloud
Connect GitHub repository → automatic deploy
Docker + Railway / Render / Fly.io

Example minimal Dockerfile:
dockerfileFROM python:3.11-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
EXPOSE 8501
HEALTHCHECK CMD curl --fail http://localhost:8501/_stcore/health || exit 1
CMD ["streamlit", "run", "app.py", "--server.port=8501", "--server.address=0.0.0.0"]
Contributing
Contributions are welcome — bug fixes, new features, documentation improvements, better models, additional cities, etc.
Development workflow

Fork the repository
Create a feature branch (git checkout -b feature/amazing-feature)
Commit your changes (git commit -m 'Add support for Novi Pazar')
Push to the branch (git push origin feature/amazing-feature)
Open a Pull Request

Coding style

Follow PEP 8
Use type hints where reasonable
Prefer @st.cache_data / @st.cache_resource for expensive operations
Keep sidebar filters clearly grouped

Pull Request Checklist

 Tests pass (or new tests added)
 Code is linted (ruff check .)
 Documentation / README updated if needed
 No large data files committed

